 authorities are seeking $772,000, which Soloway made as a result of his nefarious activities. The Federal Trade Commission received hundreds of complaints about Soloway and NIM. His offences could also earn him a $250,000 fine and five years in prison. The full statement is available Post a new comment What punishment would fit the crime? Discovery meay lead to ID theft charges as well Track this type of story as a custom Atom/RSS feed or by email. MySpace sues Spam King Former 'Spam King' pays MS $7m to settle lawsuit Spam king surrenders his ignoble crown Lawsuits drive 'Spam King' Richter to bankruptcy Spam punishment doesn't fit the crime MS moves to can more spammers The Microsoft Partner Program: Click to see your Map to Success Make IT run. Make IT safe. Run IT run. BigFix IT. Next is now! Microsoft&reg; Visual Studio 2005 Promote your Events and Training courses for free Get Started with Virtualization in 3 easy steps Try Sun servers, workstations and storage products free for 60-days Nortel is leading the evolution from TDM to IPT. Visit www.nortel.com/ipt123 Direct Attached Storage on Network Storage Advice on Enterprise Policy Management for Security and Compliance How To Demonstrate Regulatory Compliance dSPAM Standard &#8212; A dedicated junk e-mail blocking system. dSPAM Lite &#8212; A dedicated junk e-mail blocking system. CSE HTML Validator Pro &#8212; Fast, powerful, offline HTML syntax... Spyware Doctor &#8212; Spyware protection to secure your PC agains... Kensington Vo300 USB Internet Speakerphone Pharos PTL600 GPS Phone (Includes US + Canada Maps) Pharos PTL600E GPS Phone (Enterprise Edition US)* Kingston Kingston 1GB microSD Card (5 Pack) HTC S710 Smartphone (QWERTY Unlocked) Nokia N80 + Kingston 2GB MiniSD Card (Bronze Unlocked) Toshiba Portege G500 Smartphone All The Week&#8217;s Headlines
