http://news.google.com/news/url?sa=T&ct=us/12-0&fd=R&url=http://www.gamespot.com/news/6171774.html&cid=1116842054&ei=muxeRqqvDIX20AHe4M3QDQ PSP upgraded to 3.50 - News at GameSpot Registration is now open! PSP upgraded to 3.50 Sony's PlayStation Portable gets a firmware update to enable remote PS3 viewing. am PT Last week, PlayStation 3 was released, which enabled a variety of extra features for the console including adding the Remote Play ability--anyone with a PSP could then access their PS3 over the Internet. Now a firmware update for the PSP to 3.50 updates the handheld to be Remote Play ready too. Owners of both gaming machines won't be able to access DVD or Blu-ray movies or play PS3 games from their handhelds, but they will be able to access music, other videos, pictures, and their friends lists. Firmware update 3.50 also adds a RSS channel guide for PSP owners who use their portables to receive news and other RSS feeds. &laquo; Back to Today's News to post a comment on this story! I forgot I have a PSP am PT to rate this comment Javier am PT (does not meet display criteria. login to show) for god sakes there are a ton of good games for the psp so the ds fanboys should really shut the hell up already. not to mention that the psp is the most usefull portable device you can buy anyways, if you couldnt even play games on it at all it would still be an awesome machine. this fanboy bull#$%* really gets on my nerves. either way, most ds games are for kids 12 and under. am PT to rate this comment JEEBUS_BOGONDO am PT (does not meet display criteria. login to show) jus more room wasted on my default memory card lol am PT to rate this comment faceman420 am PT (does not meet display criteria. login to show) SWEET... I dont care what the update is, I just love updating my firmware..LOL... UPDATE UPDATE UPDATE am PT to rate this comment Trogeton am PT (does not meet display criteria. login to show) this update is good, lmao at the idiot fanboys out there. and gamespot i 