http://www.webpronews.com/topnews/2007/05/31/google-picks-up-panoramio&cid Google Picks Up Panoramio | WebProNews Breaking eBusiness and Search News Google Picks Up Panoramio on Thu, 05/31/2007 - 08:39. Panoramio has worked hand in hand with Google for a long time, but, on Wednesday evening, the relationship became more of a hand within hand sort of thing as Google acquired the company. Panoramio &ldquo;is a website that enables digital photographers to geolocate, store and organize their photographs - and to view those photographs in Google Earth and Google Maps,&rdquo; as explained by a statement from Google. The acquisition won&rsquo;t change any of that; Panoramio will continue to be a default layer in Yet, presumably because of the privacy concerns that pop up whenever Google is involved, users are being provided with the opportunity to &ldquo;opt out&rdquo; of the acquisition. Users who don&rsquo;t choose this option - or who do nothing at all - will, at the close of the deal, have their Panoramio-related data and photos transferred to the search engine giant. The acquisition will, however, &ldquo;bring many advantages to Panoramio users, starting with a better infrastructure to improve the reliability of Panoramio, more frequent updates of Panoramio&rsquo;s Google Earth layer, and more resources for some invisible tasks that take time out from working on new features,&rdquo; according to &ldquo;Jos&eacute;, Joaqu&iacute;n and Eduardo&rdquo; - Panoramio&rsquo;s three . (Joaqu&iacute;n and Eduardo are actually co-founders.) One last note - even as the $75 million deal between eBay and StumbleUpon is confirmed, we&rsquo;ve been left in the dark about the financial details of the Google-Panoramio acquisition. The terms were not disclosed, but, according to , the company was &ldquo;very (and we mean very) happy&rdquo; about the takeover. Doug is a staff writer for for the latest eBusiness news. More Articles By Doug Caverly: Online Auto Ads Don't Work? - 05/31/200