http://news.google.com/news/url?sa=T&ct=us/13-1&fd=R&url=http://www.pcmag.com/article2/0,1895,2139402,00.asp&cid=1116827601&ei=muxeRqqvDIX20AHe4M3QDQ Google Buys Its Way into Photo Sharing - News and Analysis by PC Magazine Computer & Console Gaming Google Buys Its Way into Photo Sharing Google has purchased Spanish photo-sharing site Panoramio, which will be integrated across several of its online properties, including Google Earth, Google said. The announcement was made by John Hanke, Google's director for Maps, Earth and Local, on the Google corporate blog. Terms of the deal were not announced. "We've been working with Panoramio for some time -- its photos have been a default layer in Google Earth since the beginning of the year," Hanke said. "This layer will remain in place as our teams work together toward further integrating this amazing content, generated by many, into our mapping technologies." 's key technology is its ability to allow users to "geolocate" pictures that they took, allowing them to position them on a map. In this case, the default map that the company has used has been Google Maps. The site also allows users to store and organize their pictures, similar to many other photo-sharing sites on the Web. For that reason, Google said the company was as interested in Panoramio's technology as it was its user base. "The acquisition of Panoramio will incorporate that website, its underlying technology, its content, developers, and user community into the Google Geo product mix," according to a Q&A posted to the Google site. "Panoramio will add interesting, useful content to Google products and will bolster Google's engineering and technical resources. New 'Google Gears' Allows Offline Web Apps Google Acquires Web Security Startup GreenBorder FTC to Review Google-DoubleClick Deal Google, Microsoft Mapping Software Gets Real Google: We Hold Data for Two Years For Panoramio, the company said it wanted to tie itself closer to Google. "Although the integration is already in place and functioning, we believed a deeper relationship would add value to the Panoramio experience for our users," the Google Q&A said, apparently attributing the comment to Panoramio executives. Passwords, under information, and other details will remain intact and unchanged throughout the transition, the companies said. Users will also have an option to opt out of the merger, although doing so will delete their content and user information from the Panoramio site. the acquisition of GreenBorder , which it will use to enhance its security offerings. PC Magazine Breaking News RSS feed to your feed reader so that you don't miss another headline! See all tech RSS feeds email newsletters delivered to your inbox. Its easy, just follow the steps. Want more? Check out our other newsletters Manage your newsletter subscriptions 1. Make your selections: PCMag.com Small Business Update Productwire: First Looks Update Tip of the Day 2. Select email format: 3. Enter email address: EXCLUSIVE WHITE PAPER FROM DELL With dramatic improvements in speed and coverage areas, mobile broadband provides flexibility and productivity for notebook users. Click here to read the full, free white paper! FREE OFFERS FROM OUR PARTNERS! Discover Better Tape Connectivity and Win Is your company constantly seeking ways to stand out above your competition? Storage Solutions for Small Business New! JUST RELEASED! New Diskeeper 2007 for Windows Vista, 30-day Trialware >> brought to you by PCMag.com Network New From PCMag.com's Utility Library Just released! Organize and control multiple network shares with NetShare Manager, PCMag.com's new premium download. With NetShare Manager, you can: &bull; store all of your mapped network shares &bull; connect and disconnect multiple shares with the push of a button &bull; set up profiles for home, office, etc./div> Download NetShare Manager today! PC Magazine's live, online events make you more productive at work, home, and on the go. Best of